            "q3_answer": "Baby Foot uses a strong acid blend (glycolic, lactic, salicylic) that causes dramatic skin peeling 3–7 days after — painful, embarrassing, and you can't wear sandals for a week. We use a goat milk + niacinamide hydrating formula that softens skin gradually with no peeling. Safer for sensitive skin, pregnancy, diabetes, and anyone who can't disappear for 7 days.",
            "q4_question": "Is it safe for sensitive skin, pregnancy, or diabetes?",
            "q4_answer": "Yes to all three. Our formula uses only goat milk, niacinamide, glycerin, and allantoin. Zero salicylic acid, zero glycolic acid, zero fragrance, zero essential oils. Customers with eczema, pregnant feet, and diabetic skin who couldn't use other foot peels use this safely. (Check with your doctor if you have specific concerns.)",
            "q5_question": "How long do results last?",
            "q5_answer": "One application keeps feet noticeably softer for 1–2 weeks for most people. Customers using the 3-pack as a weekly ritual maintain smooth heels indefinitely. Daily walkers, gym-goers, and people on their feet all day usually need a session every 7–10 days to maintain results.",
